<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAS SHUT-OFF VALVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The recent newscasts showing home and mobile home fires fed by gas from gas 
pipes broken by the earthquake remind me that over a year ago we installed gas 
valves that automatically shut off during earthquakes, in buildings with 160 
apartments, at a cost of thousands of dollars, for both tenant and owner 
protection. 
</P>
<P>
 Unfortunately, the Southern California Gas Co. insisted that these valves be 
removed, claiming that the Gas Co. would control gas fires from a central 
station.It's too bad the Gas Co. didn't act to save many of the recently burned 
homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Maybe the Gas Co., with the experience of the recent earthquake, should review 
this policy and be more concerned about public safety. 
</P>
<P>
 F. G. KLOCK JR. 
</P>
<P>
 Altadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
