<P>
 Fleet Seen Focusing on Layoffs to Cut Costs: Fleet Financial Group Inc., the 
largest banking company in New England, is expected to lay off more than 3,000 
employees, or more than 11% of its work force, as part of a restructuring that 
could save as much as $225 million annually, analysts said. Fleet is expected 
to release details today of the long-discussed restructuring. Fleet, based in 
Providence, R.I., is likely to close several of its 800 branches and reduce its 
subsidiaries to six from seven by consolidating New York operations, analysts 
said. 
