 Ford to Boost Production: The auto maker, enjoying strong demand for its cars 
and trucks, plans to boost its North American output by about 300,000 units 
this year, Chairman Alex Trotman said. The move will lift Ford's production 
capacity in the United States and Canada to 5.1 million units a year. Most of 
the increase will be in higher production of the restyled Ford Mustang, the new 
Ford Contour and Mercury Mystique, the F-Series pickups and the new Ford 
Windstar minivan. 
