<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICA'S BEST: MAIL THAT STICKS TO THE TOP OF YOUR MOUTH; THE PEANUT SHOP OF 
WILLIAMSBURG: P.O. BOX GN, WILLIAMSBURG, VA. 23187, (800) 637-3268, MASTERCARD, 
VISA  
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHIE JENKINS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Elvis Presley loved peanut butter -- he spread it on bread, added some bananas 
and then fried the whole thing in butter. Jack Nicholson eats peanut butter in 
bed to keep up his strength.Tom Selleck is also a peanut-butter fanatic; so is 
William F. Buckley Jr.  
</P>
<P>
 If you're nuts about peanut butter too, there's none better than that made at 
this pint-sized Peanut Shop that's been doing business the same careful way for 
24 years.  
</P>
<P>
 Easy to spread and with a taste of fresh-roasted peanuts, there's no secret 
ingredient here. It is just super-fresh meaty peanuts and perhaps a little 
salt.  
</P>
<P>
 The peanut butter costs $13.95 for three 18-ounce jars ($1 extra for orders 
west of the Mississippi) and is available in three varieties: smooth-lightly 
salted, smooth salt-free, and chunky-lightly salted. It's peanut butter for 
particular people. KATHIE JENKINS 
</P>
