<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PICO RIVERA; GROUP PETITIONS FOR SMALLER SCHOOL BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A community group has launched a campaign to trim the seven-member El Rancho 
Unified School District Board of Education to five members. 
</P>
<P>
 Leaders of the effort began circulating petitions this week to try to force an 
election on the issue.Organizers must present at least 250 valid signatures to 
the County Committee on School District Organization, which oversees changes in 
political boundaries and organization of school districts in Los Angeles 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers contend that the size of the board has led to conflicts and 
instability in the leadership of the 10,000-student district, which serves Pico 
Rivera. They point to the recent ouster of Supt. John T. Sherman, a veteran 
district employee, who was the fourth El Rancho schools chief to leave the 
district in five years. 
</P>
