<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; QUAKE AID: VACANCY LIST TO BE ASSEMBLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Housing Bank offers a free vacancy listing service for 
interested property owners. 
</P>
<P>
 The bank asks property owners to call and list their vacancies in the greater 
Los Angeles area, including Ventura, Orange, San Bernardino and Riverside 
counties. These vacancies will be incorporated into a master list and turned 
over to relief agencies assisting displaced families.  
</P>
<P>
 To submit a listing, call (800) 705-2392 from 10 a.m. to 7 p.m. Monday through 
Friday and 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Housing Bank is a disaster relief project of the Information 
and Referral Federation of Los Angeles Inc. 
</P>
