University. Pairs competition in men's A, men's B, women's A and co-ed 
divisions are scheduled for March 26, April 16, May 7 and June 16. The entry 
fee is $15 a team in advance, $17 on the day of the tournament. Information: 
(818) 812-3024. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendora Community Services is accepting registration for men's adult 
basketball leagues that begin March 28. Information: (818) 914-8232. . . . The 
county Parks and Recreation Department is sponsoring a wrestling club and 
tournament competition on Tuesday and Thursday nights at Rowland Heights Park 
for participants 10 to 18. Information: (909) 865-2401 or (818) 912-6774. . . . 
The San Gabriel Valley Kids Wrestling Club is conducting sign-ups on Mondays 
from 6:30 to 8 p.m. at the small gym at Arroyo High in El Monte. The program, 
open to boys and girls 5 to 14, teaches fundamentals and offers the opportunity 
to compete in tournaments. Information: (818) 338-6864. CALENDAR 
</P>
<P>
 The East San Gabriel Valley All-Star basketball games will be played March 19 
at Glendora High. Ron Rice of Northview will coach the boys' East team and Tim 
Stimpfel of Wilson will coach the West. Stu Sims of Covina will coach the 
girls' East team and Anne Ellwanger of Nogales will coach the West. 
</P>
<P>
 The games will include seniors from high schools from Duarte to Pomona. The 
girls' game is at 6 p.m. and the boys' game is scheduled at 8. 
</P>
<P>
 The West San Gabriel Valley All-Star games will be played March 25 at La 
Canada High. Seniors from Glendale to Monrovia will participate. The girls' 
game is at 6, the boys' game will start at 8. 
</P>
