Sports; Part C; Page 11; Column 4 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
253 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; ZAMUDIO'S ERROR SPOILS HIS STRONG PITCHING PERFORMANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joel Zamudio had only himself to blame for a wasted outing in Monroe High's 
2-1 San Fernando tournament loss to Thousand Oaks on Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
 The senior right-hander struck out 13 and walked three while limiting the 
visiting Lancers (1-0) to two hits, and also went two for three at the plate, 
but his eighth-inning throwing error on Jason Earles' bunt allowed the winning 
run to score from second base. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe (0-2) had tied the score in the bottom of the seventh to send the game 
into extra innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Littlerock 17, Paraclete 2 -- The Lobos pounded 18 hits in the nonleague game 
at Paraclete. 
</P>
<P>
 Jesse Silva went four for four with a three-run home run. Jorge Pacheco, who 
homered and tripled, was three for four. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 9, Bell-Jeff 6 -- Designated hitter Sam Rutherford went two for 
