PREP ROUNDUP; NO. 1 HUNTINGTON BEACH EASILY WINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach, the top-ranked volleyball team in Division I, easily swept 
ninth-ranked Newport Harbor, 15-10, 15-8 and 15-11 Wednesday at home. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Grave led the Oilers (1-1) with 14 kills while Mitch McCoy had a 
game-high 27 for the Sailors (0-2). Greg Slick added 15 kills for Newport 
Harbor, which played without starting setter Eric Vallely; he sat out with an 
injured knee. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
