nation. He had 100 strikeouts last season with a 1.45 earned-run average. The 
6-3 senior batted .296 and has signed with UCLA. Newcomer Puffer will also be 
on the mound and Coach Zamora expects good things from him. Capistrano Valley 
is an experienced team, with 15 seniors and one junior. Last season, the 
Cougars finished tied for third and missed a spot in the playoffs, but Zamora 
expects better results this year: "So far I don't see any weaknesses. We've 
been together a long time and we play well together." 
