<P>
 In his 14th season at the helm, Canary hopes his team finishes atop the league 
standings this season after taking second in 1993; this should be the year the 
Dolphins can do it. They return six starters and have a promising bunch of 
newcomers. "We are a well-rounded club," Canary said. "Our pitching and defense 
are both strong and we run well." The Dolphins are led by Etherton, a senior 
who was All-Division I and a Times Orange County first-team selection last 
year. Etherton led the county in strikeouts with 102. He hit six home runs 
during the regular season. Maynard, a second-team all-league pick, will be 
behind the plate when he isn't on the mound. Although only a junior, he's a top 
Division I prospect. Toomey, a junior transfer from University, pitches right 
and will play in the outfield. "He's a great player and a good prospect also," 
Canary said. Richardson returns at shortstop. Whittaker, a second-team 
all-league selection, will be back at second base, and senior Ralph, also a 
second-team all-league pick, will return to center field. 
