WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; SCHOOL TO HOLD FORUM ON SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cabrillo Middle School in Ventura will hold a forum on school safety for 
parents whose children are either entering the middle school this fall or 
graduating to high school. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled to be held from 7 to 8:30 p.m. Tuesday at the Cabrillo cafeteria, 
the forum will give parents an opportunity to get their questions about school 
safety answered by local school and police officials, Cabrillo Principal Kris 
Bergstrom said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cabrillo officials hold a parent forum early each year, but change the topic 
according to parents' main concerns at that time, Bergstrom said. 
</P>
<P>
 This year, school safety is at the forefront of many parents' minds, she said, 
because of recent violence and racial incidents at county schools. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Cabrillo at 641-5155. MAIA DAVIS 
