<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SCIENCE FAIR SEEKS VOLUNTEER JUDGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Organizers of the Ventura County Science Fair are seeking retired teachers and 
other county residents who have a background in science to serve as volunteer 
judges for the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the Ventura County Economic Development Assn. and the county 
superintendent of schools, this year's science fair will be held April 19-21 at 
the County Fairgrounds in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Students in the sixth through 12th grades in public and private schools are 
entering science projects in the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteer judges will be asked to attend an orientation and barbecue dinner in 
Camarillo on April 13, in addition to spending about four hours judging entries 
at the fairgrounds April 20. 
</P>
<P>
 The science fair will present awards in eight categories: botany; chemistry or 
biochemistry; earth, space and environment; math and computers; microbiology 
and medical science; physics; psychology, sociology and human behavior; and 
zoology and human behavior. 
</P>
<P>
 But organizers said their biggest need is for people to judge the botany 
entries. For more information, call Elaine Daugherty at 388-4411. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
