<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION: SIMI VALLEY; HOME REPAIR LOANS OFFERED TO THE 
NEEDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Needy Simi Valley residents interested in making home repairs may qualify for 
low-interest loans through the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Government-subsidized loans of up to $20,000 with interest rates as low as 4% 
are available to low- and moderate-income homeowners in Simi Valley. Loans are 
also available for mobile home owners. 
</P>
<P>
 The loans may be used to repair earthquake damage or for other home 
improvements such as painting, landscaping and adding rooms. 
</P>
<P>
 Funding for the loans is provided in part by the federal Community Development 
Block Grant program and the local Community Development Agency. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the city's Department of Environmental Services, 
Home Rehabilitation Program at 583-6757. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
