<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION: SIMI VALLEY; FREE CLINIC HONORS CHAMBER OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Simi Valley nonprofit group has honored Chamber of Commerce head Nancy 
Bender for helping link civic leaders with social service agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley Free Clinic, which provides medical, legal and counseling aid 
to needy residents, presented Bender with its second annual Spirit Award in a 
ceremony last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Bender, a former city councilwoman who has served as executive director of the 
chamber for 12 years, was chosen for the award because of a leadership training 
program she runs at the chamber, said Fred Bauermeister, executive director of 
the clinic. 
</P>
<P>
 The leadership program, which is open to the public, introduces trainees to 
various aspects of community life, including city government, the media and 
health services. The group meets once a month. 
</P>
<P>
 Bauermeister said one of last year's trainees, a local physician, was so 
impressed by the clinic that he joined the board. 
</P>
<P>
 "Nancy has really put together a great program," Bauermeister said. "It's been 
invaluable in giving the clinic the positive exposure it needs." 
</P>
<P>
 At the awards ceremony, Bender received a plaque and a $500 contribution to 
the leadership program. 
</P>
<P>
 "To be honored in this way is an absolute delight," Bender said. "It is 
something I will treasure all my life." SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
