<TEXT>
<P>
 Graveside services are scheduled Friday for Betty Jane Shattuck, a former 
elementary school principal in Ventura who died Wednesday. She was 70. 
</P>
<P>
 Shattuck, born in Whittier, came to Ventura with her family in 1937, said her 
sister, Colyn Warren of Cerritos.  
</P>
<P>
 Shattuck majored in education at Pepperdine University and went on to USC, 
where she received a master's degree in education and reading before returning 
to Ventura to teach. 
</P>
<P>
 She worked with the Ventura Unified School District for the next 35 years, 
eventually serving as principal at three Ventura elementary schools -- E.P. 
Foster, El Camino and Pierpont. She retired in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 She also taught at the Church of Christ Bible school and was active in the 
Pepperdine alumni association, her sister said. 
</P>
<P>
 She is survived by her sister, a son, Clark Shattuck of Ventura, and three 
nephews. 
</P>
<P>
 Graveside services will be held at 3 p.m. Friday at Ivy Lawn Cemetery. A 
memorial service will be held 3 p.m. Sunday at the Ventura Church of Christ. 
</P>
