<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SANTA MONICA; BUS RUNS 
OVER WOMAN, 90, WHO STUMBLED ON CURB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 90-year-old Santa Monica woman was killed Wednesday morning when she was run 
over by a bus from which she had just gotten off, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred near 4th Street and Broadway as the bus pulled away from 
a passenger stop. Santa Monica Police Sgt. Gary Gallinot said the woman 
stumbled on a curb, reached back to the moving bus for support and fell under 
the rear wheels. Her identity was withheld pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
