<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SIERRA MADRE; SEARCH 
CONTINUES FOR MAN, SON MISSING AFTER FLOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crews dug up a mud-filled catch basin Wednesday, looking for a man and his 
9-year-old son three days after they disappeared during a flash flood. 
</P>
<P>
 Searchers used shovels and backhoes to dig in the basin at Bailey Canyon 
Wilderness Park in the San Gabriel Mountains foothills, said Police Sgt. Chris 
Christensen. John Henderson, 34, and his son, Matthew, were hiking in the 
picturesque canyon Sunday when a wall of mud and water roared into the basin 
without warning. Authorities believed they were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
