<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; MTA 
SETS UP HOT LINE FOR PROSPECTIVE BUSINESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County Metropolitan Transportation Authority has launched a 
hot line for prospective business owners interested in working with the agency. 
</P>
<P>
 The line enables prospective minority and women business owners to get 
information about the certification process necessary to work for the agency.  
</P>
<P>
 The 24-hour number is (213) 244-6333. Messages will receive a response within 
48 hours. 
</P>
