<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; CITY TO 
DEMOLISH BADLY DAMAGED BUILDINGS FOR FREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an attempt to eliminate hazards stemming from the Northridge earthquake, 
Los Angeles will demolish free of charge any red-tagged buildings that suffered 
more than 50% damage. 
</P>
<P>
 Gerald Takaki, a city building official, estimated that more than 400 
apartment buildings, homes and commercial structures qualify for the free 
demolition. Officials expect the Federal Emergency Management Agency to 
compensate the city for the costs. The city carried out a similar program after 
the 1992 riots. 
</P>
<P>
 Owners wishing to have their buildings razed should contact any city 
Department of Building and Safety office or call (800) 890-0223. 
</P>
</TEXT>
