<HEADLINE>
<P>
RISKY OVERPASSES IN THE VALLEY AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three of the 10 freeway bridges judged by Caltrans to be the most seismically 
hazardous in Los Angeles County are located in the Valley area: 
</P>
<P>
 Bridges: Junction of Ventura Freeway and Golden State Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Repair Cost: $5.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Status: Design work complete. Next step is to advertise for construction bids. 
</P>
<P>
 Bridges: Junction of Ventura Freeway and Hollywood Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Repair Cost: Almost $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Status: Design work complete. Construction bids being solicited. 
</P>
<P>
 Bridges: Junction of Tujunga Wash and Ventura Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Repair Cost: $766,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Status: Design work under way. Construction bids being solicited. 
</P>
