</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PUC Refuses to Reopen PacTel Spinoff Case: The state Public Utilities 
Commission has decided not to rehear certain issues involved in the spinoff of 
Pacific Telesis Group's wireless unit. The city of Los Angeles, the consumer 
watchdog group Toward Utility Rate Normalization and other groups had urged the 
PUC, among other things, to reconsider how much money the telephone holding 
company should reimburse ratepayers for research and development into cellular 
technologies. San Francisco-based PacTel said its board will take a final vote 
on the spinoff in the next few days. 
</P>
