</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 General Instrument Being Investigated: The Justice Department is investigating 
whether General Instrument Corp., a leading supplier of cable TV equipment, has 
a stranglehold on the market for advanced video services, the New York Times 
reported.People familiar with the probe say the department's antitrust division 
has demanded information from the Chicago-based company about its relationships 
with the cable industry and its technology, the story said. A General 
Instrument spokesman declined to comment. Justice Department spokeswoman Gina 
Talamona said only that the antitrust division was conducting an investigation 
of arrangements that affect the cable industry, the paper said, and would not 
discuss which companies are being looked at. 
</P>
