<P>
BRIEFCASE: MARKETING / MEDIA; A SUPER BOWL STAR DETOURS TO DISNEYLAND ON INFO 
SUPERHIGHWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Emmitt Smith, star running back for the Dallas Cowboys, found that the road 
from the Super Bowl leads to the information superhighway. 
</P>
<P>
 The morning after the Cowboys' victory over the Buffalo Bills, Smith announced 
in commercials aired during the "Today" show and "Good Morning America," "I'm 
going to Disneyland!" 
</P>
<P>
 The overnight turnaround was made possible by fiber-optic splitting. Western 
International Media's Spot Link division edited the Smith commercial overnight 
for the theme park and transmitted it to the TV networks using fiber-optics. 
</P>
