<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: BIOMERICA UNIT IS ISSUED A PATENT FOR ALLERGY TREATMENT 
METHOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Biomerica Inc. said its Allergy Immuno Technologies Inc. unit has been issued 
a patent for a new method of treating allergies. 
</P>
<P>
 In a press release, the company said the latest patent covers an invention 
under which an allergen -- the material to which a patient is allergic -- is 
combined with something called a biological response modifier. The patent 
covers a class of such modifiers. 
</P>
<P>
 Biomerica said it plans to enter a "collaborative arrangement" with a drug 
company to use the invention. In the meantime, the company said, it intends to 
raise funds necessary for its allergy unit to begin marketing the new 
treatments. 
</P>
