<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; ASSEMBLYWOMAN TO BE HONORED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Assemblywoman Doris Allen (R-Cypress) is scheduled to be honored today as the 
county's Legislator of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
 The cities of Los Alamitos and Westminster nominated Allen for the award 
because they said she supports local government and is responsive to city and 
district concerns.The cities also lauded Allen for her opposition to the 
state's shifting of property-tax revenue away from local government. 
</P>
<P>
 Cities rely on property taxes, which are collected by the state and 
redistributed. In recent years, the state has given cities a smaller amount of 
the money. 
</P>
<P>
 Allen, a 14-year member of the Assembly, said she will continue fighting to 
keep property taxes flowing back to cities. 
</P>
<P>
 Allen serves on the Assembly's Ways and Means Committee, which rules on the 
state budget. She also sits on the Education Committee and the Natural 
Resources Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 The county's division of the League of California Cities is scheduled to 
recognize Allen today at a meeting. WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
