<TEXT>
<P>
 In a surprise move, Ralphs Grocery Co. has canceled its controversial plans to 
build a 40,000-square-foot store in Acton, county officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ralphs officials said they would not comment until next week on the reason for 
their decision.The announcement came the day before a hearing was scheduled on 
the proposal. 
</P>
<P>
 "Needless to say, it's highly unusual to get this close to a decision and 
withdraw, especially after they've had one hearing," said Dave Vannatta, 
planning deputy for County Supervisor Michael Antonovich. 
</P>
<P>
 The store faced opposition from many Acton residents fearful of 
overdevelopment in their rural community. 
</P>
<P>
 They asked Ralphs to scale back proposed operating hours from always open to a 
6 a.m. to midnight schedule, to limit signs advertising alcohol sales and 
provide security. 
</P>
<P>
 After first balking, Ralphs agreed to the requests. A public hearing had been 
scheduled for Thursday. 
