<P>
CHARITY SCORECARD / BEA MAXWELL: WOMEN IN FILM RICHER BY $21,000 AFTER 'ANGIE' 
SCREENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BEA MAXWELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Women in Film netted $21,000 at its premiere screening of "Angie" at the Avco 
Cinema Westwood on Feb. 28. WIF President Joan Hyler, Executive Director 
Harriet Silverman and Director Martha Coolidge celebrated the event with 
"Angie" star Geena Davis at an after-party at the Armand Hammer Museum. 
Proceeds will benefit film programs for women. 
</P>
<P>
