<P>
 The biggest addition to Westminster's lineup is Montgomery, a junior transfer 
from Fountain Valley. Montgomery had 29 runs batted during the regular season 
to help the Barons win the league championship. Montgomery will hit third in 
the lineup, pitch and play third base. He had five hits in Westminster's first 
two games, a 7-6 loss to Long Beach Jordan and a 7-2 victory over Bolsa Grande. 
Matlock returns to play shortstop after hitting .325 in a half-season last 
year. He missed the second half last season after a pitched ball broke his his 
hand. Valles led off last season and hit .365. Rodriguez returns at catcher and 
will alternate hitting fourth or fifth with Glasby, who had 24 RBIs for the 
junior varsity team, which finished 17-6 last season. But Batesole will depend 
on defense to keep the Lions close. Said Batesole: "If everybody stays healthy 
and Sorensen, Montgomery, Torres and Berumen give us solid pitching, we could 
make a run at a playoff berth." 
</P>
