<P>
 Hard-throwing right handers Jon Ward (Cal State Fullerton) and Ryan Brannan 
(Miami) have led the Oilers in the past two seasons, and now it's Dillard's 
turn. Dillard doesn't fit the profile physically--he pitches left-handed and is 
6-foot-2, 175 pounds--but Dodd hopes Dillard can lead the staff. "He's not a 
strikeout pitcher, but we don't want him to try to strike everybody out," Dodd 
said. "We want him to get the ball to guys who will make the plays for us." One 
of those players is shortstop Daedelow, a three-year starter and first-team 
all-league selection. Center fielder Yadrick, who played running back for the 
football team, is also a key defensive player. "I'm a little nervous about this 
season," Dodd said. "We have a good little ball club, but the league is so 
strong. But we always know that in a 14-game league season, the most talented 
team may not always win it." 
</P>
