<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL '94: SUNSET LEAGUE; EDISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS:  
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 21-6 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 12-2 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Paul Harrell 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 87-65-3 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T Todd 
Belitz Sr. P/1B L-L Greg Hanoian Jr. OF L-L Justin Haugen Sr. C R-R Jamie 
Surdock Sr. SS/P R-R TOP RETURNERS YR. POS. B-T Tom Barilla Sr. P/OF L-L Jeremy 
Disney Sr. C R-R Brice Keyser Sr. 3B R-R Ryan Langdon Jr. C/DH R-R TOP 
NEWCOMERS YR. POS. B-T Matt Barcellona Jr. 3B R-R Randy Beebe Sr. OF R-R Travis 
Clutter Jr. SS R-R Jeff Gonterman Jr. OF L-L OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers return four starters from last season's Sunset runner-up team, 
including two of the league's best pitchers. Belitz, the team's best 
power-hitter, is a hard-throwing lefty who shared league MVP honors with 
Fountain Valley pitcher Brian Ponchak. Surdock, a second-team all-league 
selection last season, also plays shortstop. "There's not a better 1-2 
combination than Belitz and Surdock," Huntington Beach Coach Mike Dodd said. 
And Barilla, another lefty, gives the Chargers added depth. Said Harrell: "Of 
our 21 victories last year, we have pitchers coming back that had 16 of those." 
Hanoian returns at the top of the lineup after earning first-team all-league 
honors as a sophomore. Robert Caton, a first-team all-league third baseman, 
graduated but Keyser will try to replace him. "We have the potential for a good 
year," Harrell said. Sunset coaches agree, pegging Fountain Valley, Edison and 
Marina as the favorites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
